 of names, crossing out some of them by means of an incredibly sharp pencil. The President hovered over him in a mixed state of curiosity and concern. Now and then Dr Alexander would stop to ponder, his unoccupied hand cautiously stroking the sleek fair hair at the back of his head.

'What about Rufel?' (Political Science) asked the President. 'Could you not get him?'

'Not available,' replied Dr Alexander. 'Apparently arrested. For his own safety, I am told.'

'Let us hope so,' said old Azureus